org.safs.staf

Interface STAFHelperCompatibleInterface

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSTAFHelperCompatible, STAFHelperCompatible2, STAFHelperCompatible3

    public interface STAFHelperCompatibleInterface
     This interface contains some methods need by #STAFHelper, but can't
 be defined there due to the compatibility of STAF.
 From STAF3, there are some new classes that don't exist for STAF2. If we use
 them in STAFHelper, the ClassNotFoundException will be thrown with STAF2 environment.

      • getServiceEvents

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> getServiceEvents(java.lang.String machine,
                                                java.lang.String servicename)
                                                  throws SAFSException
        According to the service name, we try to get all events related to it.
        Parameters:
        servicename - String, the service we want to get events for
        Returns:
        List of events related to the service, each list-item contains the event's name, state, number of waiters. The format is not the same for STAF2 and STAF3
        Throws:
        SAFSException

      • getRunningEngineNames

        java.util.Collection getRunningEngineNames(java.lang.String machine)
                                           throws SAFSException
        Get collection of running Engine names. We parse the STAF command: staf local SEM list EVENT
        We deduce the number of unique <engine>Ready or <engine>Running events. We return the collection of unique engine names.
        Returns:
        Collection (Vector) of String engine names( ex: SAFS/RobotJ, SAFS/SELENIUM, etc..)
        Throws:
        SAFSException
